law.text:
It shall be a misdemeanor for any person to:
Sell or fraudulently obtain or furnish any license or aid or abet therein;
Practice as a long-term care administrator, under cover of any license illegally or fraudulently obtained or unlawfully issued;
Practice as a long-term care administrator or use in connection with his or her name any designation tending to imply that he or she is a long-term care administrator unless duly licensed to so practice under the provisions of this chapter; or
Practice as a long-term care administrator during the time his or her license issued under the provisions of this chapter shall be suspended or revoked.
